Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.01,0:00:08.82,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,Good evening, Prince Theodore.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.30,0:00:13.49,main,Theodore,0,0,0,,Good evening, my lovely older sister.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.49,0:00:15.22,main,Theodore,0,0,0,,Impressive.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.22,0:00:17.99,main,Theodore,0,0,0,,From your demeanor, I take \Nit you knew it would be me?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.90,0:00:21.75,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,If you would like to speak, \NI ask that it be brief.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.91,0:00:24.60,main,Theodore,0,0,0,,Continuing from this morning,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.60,0:00:27.63,main,Theodore,0,0,0,,you don't know my older brother \Nvery well yet, do you?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.41,0:00:31.84,main,Theodore,0,0,0,,So I'll tell you about him.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.11,0:00:37.30,main,Theodore,0,0,0,,My older brother thinks \Nnothing of killing people.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.30,0:00:38.89,main,Theodore,0,0,0,,That's the kind of person he is.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.76,0:00:41.52,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,I know that.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.52,0:00:44.58,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,Arnold Hein committed massacres \Nin other countries...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.58,0:00:47.52,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,and invaded every nation in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.77,0:00:51.78,main,Theodore,0,0,0,,And, of course, I'm not \Nspeaking of times of war.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.78,0:00:53.41,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.00,0:00:57.50,main,Theodore,0,0,0,,You see, my brother...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.00,0:01:00.41,main,Theodore,0,0,0,,killed his own mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.37,0:01:03.41,main,Theodore,0,0,0,,A horrifying story, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.41,0:01:05.85,main,Theodore,0,0,0,,Striking down his own mother?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.85,0:01:07.79,main,Theodore,0,0,0,,There's nothing decent about that, is there?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.72,0:01:11.58,main,Theodore,0,0,0,,And one day, you'll be killed, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.05,0:01:13.92,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,Is there something wrong with that?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.33,0:01:16.47,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,For my part...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.93,0:01:21.05,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,I am fully aware of the facts, and I \Nchoose to become Prince Arnold's bride.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.60,0:02:56.53,main,Theodore,0,0,0,,{\an8}Did you hear what I said?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.53,0:02:58.58,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,{\an8}I'm not surprised.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.58,0:03:02.78,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,He's the person who will one day kill \Nhis father and usurp the throne.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.78,0:03:04.94,main,Theodore,0,0,0,,You don't understand anything!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.94,0:03:07.92,main,Theodore,0,0,0,,My brother is a heartless man\Nwho neither cries nor bleeds!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.59,0:03:10.41,top,Rishe,0,0,0,,It seems our talk is at an end. You should \Ncontinue this conversation with your brother.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.84,0:03:15.99,main,Theodore,0,0,0,,Brother...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.92,0:03:21.10,main,Theodore,0,0,0,,Why is my brother here?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.10,0:03:24.11,main,Theodore,0,0,0,,This is a misunderstanding! What I said \Njust now isn't what I really think!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.11,0:03:25.66,main,Theodore,0,0,0,,It's all a misunderstanding!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.72,0:03:28.06,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,Theodore.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.54,0:03:32.34,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,I believe I ordered you \Nto stay away from Rishe.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.84,0:03:39.60,main,Theodore,0,0,0,,I'm sorry, brother.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.60,0:03:40.98,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,Let's go, Rishe.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.07,0:03:45.51,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,Please wait, Your Highness. Speak with \Nyour brother for a moment or two.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.51,0:03:46.56,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,There's no need.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.56,0:03:47.16,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.36,0:03:48.34,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,Rishe.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.20,0:03:52.03,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,Yes, Your Highness.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.29,0:04:03.37,main,Theodore,0,0,0,,It truly is just as I thought, my sister.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.22,0:04:08.87,main,Theodore,0,0,0,,I'm really sorry, brother.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.87,0:04:12.28,main,Theodore,0,0,0,,I won't say anything mean \Nto your dear bride any more.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.80,0:04:16.27,main,Theodore,0,0,0,,Good night.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.27,0:04:19.81,main,Theodore,0,0,0,,It's been a while since I've seen you \Nup close like this. It made me happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.39,0:04:29.29,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,And I believe I told you as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.49,0:04:34.54,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,Since your name was used to call me here, \NPrince Arnold, I couldn't simply ignore it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.54,0:04:37.10,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,Though, I did take a bit of \Na gamble on your coming here.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.42,0:04:42.46,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,I received a reply to a letter I never sent.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.46,0:04:48.26,sign_generic,text,0,0,0,,{\bord1\blur1\an7\fs18\fade(1,200)\pos(8.923,259.701)}Thank you for your\Ninvitation. I will go to\Nthe chapel alone at\Nhalf-past twelve as\Nspecified.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.83,0:04:45.41,top,Arnold,0,0,0,,I would have been crazy to sit \Nback and relax after that.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.41,0:04:48.26,top,Rishe,0,0,0,,Thank you for coming for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.76,0:04:52.89,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.82,0:04:57.77,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,Why do people say you're a cruel person?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.88,0:05:01.15,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,Probably because it's the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.42,0:05:05.50,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,In the last war, Your \NHighness took many lives,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.50,0:05:11.05,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,but from what I've seen of you in this \Ncountry, you are a considerate, kind person.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.15,0:05:14.97,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,It seems I've looked after you too well.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.66,0:05:23.91,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,If you wish to survive in this palace, \Ndiscard that naïve mindset immediately.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.28,0:05:28.34,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,I trust what I've seen.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.34,0:05:31.81,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,You've never seen me on the battlefield. \NYou don't know what you're saying.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.81,0:05:36.44,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,The person who has shown me such care and \Nconsideration was also undeniably you, wasn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.72,0:05:38.20,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,Don't be ridiculous.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.20,0:05:41.23,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,I brought you here to use you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.23,0:05:46.13,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,Even so, I can't think of \Nyou as a cruel person...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.81,0:05:48.98,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,my husband.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.58,0:06:01.40,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,What is this resolve you carry within you?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.40,0:06:03.12,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,Resolve?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.53,0:06:05.84,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,I see it in your eyes sometimes.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.35,0:06:08.84,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,They're the eyes of someone \Nstanding on a battlefield.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.84,0:06:13.45,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,"If it means that I can stay true to my \Nconvictions, then I don't care if I die here."
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.45,0:06:16.23,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,You have the eyes of someone \Nwith that sort of resolve.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.88,0:06:19.67,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,Even then, you haven't given up on surviving.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.67,0:06:22.62,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,You will fight until the very last.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.62,0:06:27.04,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,The moments when I had \Nto kill such a person...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.04,0:06:29.61,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,were the most terrifying moments of the war.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.28,0:06:33.61,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,He has things that frighten him, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.58,0:06:41.23,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,I have dreams where I am killed.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.23,0:06:44.75,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,When I wake, I know that \NI'm alive, here and now.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.18,0:06:48.33,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,But sometimes, I feel very afraid.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.33,0:06:49.26,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,Afraid?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.63,0:06:55.31,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,I worry that the truth is I've died \Nand that the world I'm living in now
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.31,0:06:58.95,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,is just a long dream I'm \Nhaving after my death.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.64,0:07:03.16,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,I didn't realize I had \Nthese feelings inside me.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.80,0:07:06.66,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,Pay it no mind. What does \Nit matter if I'm scared?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.87,0:07:10.89,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,Even so, I've made up my mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.89,0:07:15.53,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,No matter how this life may \Nend, I don't want to run away.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.73,0:07:19.88,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,What I carry within me now is the \Nresolve to live as your wife.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.88,0:07:21.49,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,No more than that.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.01,0:07:50.06,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,You fool.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.02,0:07:55.90,main,Arnold,0,0,0,,The resolve to be my wife? \NThere's no need for that.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.93,0:08:30.30,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,What was that yesterday?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.46,0:08:34.66,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,And...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.14,0:08:39.00,flashback,Arnold,0,0,0,,The resolve to be my wife? \NThere's no need for that.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.02,0:08:42.30,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,What did those words mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.83,0:08:48.38,main,Elsie,0,0,0,,Lady Rishe, did you not \Nsleep again last night?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.38,0:08:49.91,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,Elsie.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.91,0:08:52.12,main,Elsie,0,0,0,,You've been working too \Nhard the past few days.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.12,0:08:54.38,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,I'm all right. No need to worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.79,0:08:58.22,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,I say that, but I think I've \Nfinally reached my limits.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.92,0:09:07.49,main,Elsie,0,0,0,,So sparkly and smooth...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.08,0:09:11.91,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,This is the merchandise I'm \Nproposing to Chief Tully.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.91,0:09:13.24,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,And what perfect timing!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.64,0:09:15.30,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,Will you sit there for me?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.66,0:09:21.25,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,In the east, they have a custom of staining\Ntheir nails with dyes made from flowers.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.25,0:09:25.75,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,I used that as a hint and tried adding \Ncolor to nail-strengthening medicine.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.75,0:09:30.22,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,I thought that this way, you could enjoy \Nbeing stylish even while scrubbing and washing.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.22,0:09:32.64,main,Elsie,0,0,0,,This will make my nails stronger?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.64,0:09:35.26,main,Elsie,0,0,0,,Mine always split right away.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.26,0:09:37.76,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,This should make them less likely to split.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.23,0:09:41.85,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,But the most important thing \Nis to eat meat or fish.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.85,0:09:44.02,main,Elsie,0,0,0,,Meat. Fish.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.75,0:09:46.00,main,Elsie,0,0,0,,I'll remember that.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.00,0:09:48.52,main,Elsie,0,0,0,,From now on, I'll be able \Nto use my pay to get some.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.01,0:09:51.10,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,Elsie, if I remember \Ncorrectly, your family is...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.10,0:09:53.68,main,Elsie,0,0,0,,Yes, my family is poor.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.68,0:09:57.28,main,Elsie,0,0,0,,It's all I can do to feed my \Nyounger brother and sister.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.46,0:10:02.03,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,So this nation has a deeply \Nrooted poverty problem, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.91,0:10:05.66,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,There are households like Elsie's here.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.38,0:10:15.12,main,Elsie,0,0,0,,It's so beautiful.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.79,0:10:19.30,main,Elsie,0,0,0,,I've never seen anything so sparkly.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.73,0:10:21.62,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,Elsie, do you have a favorite color?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.06,0:10:23.43,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,I'd like to give you a present.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.43,0:10:25.73,main,Elsie,0,0,0,,I-I couldn't possibly!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.73,0:10:28.71,main,Elsie,0,0,0,,If I accepted something \Nas wonderful as this...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.71,0:10:32.01,main,Elsie,0,0,0,,I believe I should restrain myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.01,0:10:36.19,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,Not at all! Elsie, your using \Nthis would make me happy, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.64,0:10:40.20,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,What color would you like?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.57,0:10:44.15,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,Any color would suit you very \Nwell. Won't you tell me?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.52,0:10:51.56,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,Elsie?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.23,0:10:56.93,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,Wh-What's wrong? Does something hurt?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.80,0:11:01.05,main,Elsie,0,0,0,,I'm... happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.72,0:11:06.15,main,Elsie,0,0,0,,I don't know how to thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.62,0:11:10.71,main,Elsie,0,0,0,,I'm just... so very happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.96,0:11:13.06,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,Elsie.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.91,0:11:20.42,main,Elsie,0,0,0,,My family is very poor, and our \Nclothes are always in tatters.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.42,0:11:22.59,main,Elsie,0,0,0,,We could never dress fashionably.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.42,0:11:27.48,main,Elsie,0,0,0,,And now, I've not only become \Nyour maid, Lady Rishe,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.48,0:11:30.23,main,Elsie,0,0,0,,I'm to be given something so beautiful...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.88,0:11:32.49,main,Elsie,0,0,0,,I'm just so happy!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.50,0:11:37.59,main,maids; background,0,0,0,,That's amazing! It's so pretty!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.34,0:11:45.35,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,There are other girls in this \Ncountry doing what Elsie did,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.35,0:11:49.69,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,suppressing their own longings and \Ndreams for the sake of their families.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.49,0:11:53.38,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.85,0:11:56.07,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,Right now, I'm not a merchant.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.52,0:11:59.08,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,Right now, I am...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.79,0:12:11.00,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,Most of the people coming in and out of the \Ncapital are working men in their prime.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.36,0:12:13.75,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,So, I thought this would \Nmake the perfect souvenir.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.02,0:12:16.13,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,And it's a small bottle, \Nso it won't be unwieldy.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.33,0:12:25.03,main,Tully,0,0,0,,Magnificent!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.03,0:12:28.18,main,Tully,0,0,0,,What genius conceived of these wares?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.18,0:12:31.21,main,Tully,0,0,0,,I'm certain that many women will want it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.21,0:12:34.10,main,Tully,0,0,0,,Please allow our trading \Ncompany to handle the sales.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.10,0:12:36.80,main,Chester,0,0,0,,All right! Let's start promoting \Nit to our clients right away!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.80,0:12:37.90,main,Tully,0,0,0,,Now, just wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.84,0:12:42.08,main,Tully,0,0,0,,If this product were \Nentrusted to us right now,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.08,0:12:45.58,main,Tully,0,0,0,,we'd sell it as a highly priced \Nproduct intended for nobles.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.14,0:12:50.51,main,Tully,0,0,0,,But it seems that Lady \NRishe has a different idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.50,0:12:55.17,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,Yes. This is where our \Nbusiness discussion begins.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.25,0:13:03.05,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,Three years ago, Prince Arnold established \Na minimum wage in this country.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.05,0:13:06.76,main,Tully,0,0,0,,I see. So, that policy \Nwas the crown prince's?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.18,0:13:13.93,main,Tully,0,0,0,,However, this boon is granted only to \Nthose who can find employment, I believe.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.18,0:13:15.22,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.22,0:13:20.55,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,This item isn't costly or difficult to make.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.55,0:13:23.32,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,However, it will require a lot of \Nmanpower to create large amounts.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.68,0:13:25.60,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,I have a suggestion in that area.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.60,0:13:27.57,main,Tully,0,0,0,,Please allow me to hear it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.27,0:13:31.33,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,Large scale hiring from the slums.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.26,0:13:36.93,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,If you promise me that this will \Nbe done, and only if you promise,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.93,0:13:39.51,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,then I will provide you the \Ntechnique to create this item.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.51,0:13:42.46,main,Tully,0,0,0,,What a magnificent idea!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.04,0:13:45.27,main,Tully,0,0,0,,However...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.46,0:13:54.72,main,Tully,0,0,0,,I'm disappointed in you, Miss Rishe.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.72,0:13:57.52,main,Kamil,0,0,0,,Kaine Tully, how dare you be so insolent!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.52,0:13:58.63,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,It's all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.55,0:14:01.18,main,Tully,0,0,0,,If you wish to perform charitable acts,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.18,0:14:04.94,main,Tully,0,0,0,,please feel free to wait until I change \Nprofessions and become a clergyman.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.20,0:14:08.20,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,Chief, this is a business proposal.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.89,0:14:15.32,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,After the war, Galkhein created a number \Nof policies to benefit its people.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.32,0:14:20.42,main,Tully,0,0,0,,And thanks to those, people's income increased,\Nand their lives became more extravagant?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.42,0:14:24.71,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,Yes. However, there are people \Nwho don't receive these benefits.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.21,0:14:29.22,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,Unless some method is provided for them to \Naccess these means, the economy will stagnate,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.55,0:14:32.72,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,and one day, it will lead \Nto a drop in tax revenue.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.42,0:14:40.04,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,In other words, we share a common destiny \Nwithin this cyclical loop known as the economy.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.70,0:14:42.98,main,Tully,0,0,0,,So basically, this is what \Nyou're trying to say...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.42,0:14:47.30,main,Tully,0,0,0,,Keeping riches isolated in one \Nplace won't create abundance.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.30,0:14:50.00,main,Tully,0,0,0,,In which case, we should \Nshare them with the poor.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.00,0:14:50.99,main,Tully,0,0,0,,Is that right?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.30,0:14:55.50,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,A long time ago, someone said this to me...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.58,0:15:00.25,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,"First-class merchants can \Nchoose their customers."
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.57,0:15:04.34,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,But, Chief...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.09,0:15:08.68,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,instead of choosing our customers,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.68,0:15:11.02,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,why don't we produce them ourselves?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.60,0:15:22.78,main,Tully,0,0,0,,I see! I like it!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.78,0:15:26.98,main,Tully,0,0,0,,So, what you're saying is, "Don't choose \Nyour customers, cultivate them yourself"!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.41,0:15:29.88,main,Chester,0,0,0,,What's that mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.58,0:15:35.53,main,Tully,0,0,0,,If the people of the slums can earn an \Nincome, they'll become our customers.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.53,0:15:39.92,main,Tully,0,0,0,,As their number increases, merchants' \Nsales will increase as a result.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.92,0:15:41.94,main,Tully,0,0,0,,That's the hidden motivation here.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.94,0:15:44.88,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,All of your company's wares are splendid.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.88,0:15:48.70,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,The ones who will see the greatest profits \Nin this market of newly created customers
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.70,0:15:50.88,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,will be the Aria Trading Company.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.88,0:15:52.43,top,Chester; background,0,0,0,,So that's what you mean!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.52,0:15:53.66,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,So their lives aren't only \Nabout having enough to eat
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.43,0:15:53.66,top,Chester; background,0,0,0,,Sounds good, doesn't it, Chief?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.66,0:15:55.63,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,and so they don't have \Nto give up their dreams,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.66,0:15:55.63,top,Melvin; background,0,0,0,,Creating our own market...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.63,0:15:59.03,top,Melvin; background,0,0,0,,I think it's an intriguing idea. \NI'd like to be a part of that!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.14,0:16:00.17,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,I want this country to become one that \Nturns the despair of the slums into hope.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.17,0:16:03.55,top,Tully; background,0,0,0,,Honestly, you're both getting \Nahead of yourselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.14,0:16:03.55,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,Right now, what I should be \Ndoing as the crown princess
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.55,0:16:08.10,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,is creating businesses that will bring \Nprosperity to the people of this country.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.64,0:16:13.53,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,This is one of the few proposals I can \Noffer you in my current circumstances.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.53,0:16:15.48,main,Tully,0,0,0,,Not bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.48,0:16:19.91,main,Tully,0,0,0,,You seemed to have seen through me, right to \Nmy convictions, so this has been entertaining.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.65,0:16:24.17,main,Tully,0,0,0,,But, Miss Rishe, you're still immature.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.09,0:16:27.73,main,Tully,0,0,0,,Your behavior is much too earnest.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.73,0:16:30.42,main,Tully,0,0,0,,It seems you really want \Nto work with our company.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.87,0:16:37.30,main,Tully,0,0,0,,I could use that fixation of yours to wring \Nyou dry. I've already started plotting how.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.30,0:16:39.31,main,Chester,0,0,0,,Chief, you're going too far.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.31,0:16:44.24,main,Tully,0,0,0,,Now, shall I begin finding \Nfaults in your proposal?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.24,0:16:46.13,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,A proposal made by the likes of me?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.13,0:16:48.94,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,I never believed that you'd \Nunreservedly approve of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.94,0:16:52.32,main,Tully,0,0,0,,Really? We've only met a handful of times.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.32,0:16:55.32,main,Tully,0,0,0,,It makes me happy that you \Nalready understand me so well.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.48,0:17:00.39,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,I wanted to avoid using \Nthis if possible, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.40,0:17:07.21,main,Tully,0,0,0,,Well! What will appear from \Nyour bag of tricks next—
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.00,0:17:12.94,main,Melvin,0,0,0,,Chief?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.78,0:17:17.66,main,Tully,0,0,0,,How?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.90,0:17:20.97,main,Tully,0,0,0,,How do you have this?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.81,0:17:23.54,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,I'm very sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.54,0:17:27.73,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,I used a rather special \Nmethod to look into this.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.72,0:17:32.73,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,And into your younger sister, \NAria Tully's, illness.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.42,0:17:39.24,main,Tully,0,0,0,,There's nothing strange \Nabout word of Aria leaking.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.71,0:17:42.80,main,Tully,0,0,0,,After all, I've gone around speaking \Nto different doctors about her.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.16,0:17:47.92,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,At the moment, I am cultivating \Na number of medicinal plants.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.64,0:17:51.92,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,Compounding the plants according \Nto the method written there
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.38,0:17:56.54,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,will create a medicine from the \Nlarge eastern country of Renhua...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.81,0:18:00.68,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,a medicine effective against \NMiss Aria's illness.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.11,0:18:05.86,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,If she takes this medicine for a year,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.86,0:18:08.02,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,she should make a profound recovery.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.03,0:18:11.21,main,Tully,0,0,0,,And you think I'd believe you?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.21,0:18:13.80,main,Tully,0,0,0,,You're not a doctor. No \Nmatter what you say, I—
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.93,0:18:17.07,top,Rishe,0,0,0,,Did the medicine I gave you \Nthe other day help all of you?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.71,0:18:22.22,flashback,Rishe,0,0,0,,When everyone wakes, please \Nhave them drink this medicine.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.17,0:18:25.88,main,Melvin,0,0,0,,It did. I had a horrible hangover,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.88,0:18:28.16,main,Melvin,0,0,0,,but after I drank that, \NI felt better right away.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.52,0:18:30.87,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,That was something I concocted myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.30,0:18:39.04,main,Tully,0,0,0,,"Become a merchant who can \Nchoose your own customers."
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.48,0:18:43.08,main,Tully,0,0,0,,That's what I've told my \Nsubordinates all this time.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.46,0:18:47.43,main,Tully,0,0,0,,You've turned the tables on me, Miss Rishe.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.29,0:18:52.95,main,Tully,0,0,0,,Up until now, this maneuvering was all \Nabout whether I'd choose you or not.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.95,0:18:56.82,main,Tully,0,0,0,,But now, it's about whether you'll choose me.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.82,0:18:57.90,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,Chief...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.15,0:19:04.20,main,Tully,0,0,0,,I'm begging you. I'll give \Nyou everything I own.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.63,0:19:06.63,main,Tully,0,0,0,,Please, give this medicine to—
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.63,0:19:09.19,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,Please don't misunderstand me.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.75,0:19:13.37,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,I'll give you the method and the medicinal \Nherbs needed without any conditions.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.05,0:19:16.92,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,I have no intention of using \Nyour sister to my advantage.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.62,0:19:20.76,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,But I would like for you to understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.76,0:19:25.56,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,The people of the slums care \Nabout their families, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.37,0:19:29.18,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,To make sure their younger \Nsiblings don't fall ill...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.18,0:19:30.80,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,to make sure that they can feed them...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.80,0:19:36.07,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,so many older brothers and sisters \Nsacrifice their own dreams.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.53,0:19:41.82,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,This clumsy method was the only way \NI could bring my proposal to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.38,0:19:45.83,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,I don't believe that the tables have turned.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.97,0:19:50.74,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,Please, will you help me, Chief Tully?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.74,0:19:56.86,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,Won't you please enter into \N business with me?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.20,0:20:15.86,main,Tully,0,0,0,,Please, lift your head, Lady Rishe.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.86,0:20:18.48,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,Chief Tully! Please don't do that!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.48,0:20:23.23,main,Tully,0,0,0,,Trade is meant to bring abundance \Nto everyone involved,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.88,0:20:26.08,main,Tully,0,0,0,,but I thought to choose my customers.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.81,0:20:28.62,main,Tully,0,0,0,,It is I who am truly immature here.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.20,0:20:31.69,main,Tully,0,0,0,,Until now, the fates of people in the slums
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.69,0:20:35.12,main,Tully,0,0,0,,have never meant anything to \Nme. That's the honest truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.34,0:20:39.94,main,Tully,0,0,0,,But there are many children \Nlike my sister living there.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.57,0:20:48.01,main,Tully,0,0,0,,Your business idea is worth far more than \Nanything someone like me could think up.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.47,0:20:54.86,main,Tully,0,0,0,,Even aside from the matter of my sister's \Nmedicine, I feel ashamed of my own arrogance.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.85,0:20:57.02,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,Then, Chief, you'll...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.65,0:21:06.19,main,Tully,0,0,0,,From this moment on, the Aria Trading \NCompany, in the name of Kaine Tully,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.19,0:21:09.25,main,Tully,0,0,0,,will prepare everything you have asked for.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.21,0:21:13.44,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,Thank you so much!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.59,0:21:23.56,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,It was like walking a tightrope.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.56,0:21:25.26,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,I'm so glad it all turned out well.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.09,0:21:29.43,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,But I can't just sit here pleased with myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.43,0:21:30.92,italics,Rishe; internal,0,0,0,,I must prepare for what comes next.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.01,0:21:34.64,main,Kamil,0,0,0,,Lady Rishe!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.64,0:21:35.36,main,Dennis,0,0,0,,Are you all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.36,0:21:36.90,main,Kamil,0,0,0,,Are you feeling unwell?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.89,0:21:39.19,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.42,0:21:45.45,main,Rishe,0,0,0,,Could you call Elsie back for me please?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.52,0:21:47.45,main,Kamil; Dennis,0,0,0,,Yes, my lady!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.07,0:21:50.58,main,Oliver,0,0,0,,How is Lady Rishe faring?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.85,0:21:52.79,main,Dennis,0,0,0,,Her condition seems very poor.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.79,0:21:55.66,main,Dennis,0,0,0,,Kamil and her maid Elsie \Nare seeing to her now.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.16,0:21:58.20,main,Oliver,0,0,0,,Lady Rishe!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.71,0:22:14.68,main,Dominic,0,0,0,,We've awaited your arrival.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.47,0:22:19.69,main,Theodore,0,0,0,,It's just so perfect for us that she \Nbecame indisposed and collapsed!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.62,0:22:23.70,main,Theodore,0,0,0,,Thank you, Kamil, Elsie...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.41,0:22:31.78,main,Theodore,0,0,0,,for abducting the future \Ncrown princess for me.
